>                                                                  then
>         filter it
>                  on "flag" and
>                                    "mapq". Then I
>                                                     subset the
>                                                                  resulting
>                  GAlignments in
>                           a minus
>                                    and a plus
>                                                     -strand object.
>                                                                  Then I
>         calculate
>                  coverage
>                           by my own
>                                                     coverage function which
>                                                                  uses
>         the cigar
>
>         information in the
>                           GAlignments
>                                    object. This
>                                                     function is the
>                                                                  one using
>
>         cigarToRleList()
>                  at the
>                           moment. As I
>                                                     understand the
>
>         coverage() function
>                                                                  from the
>                           GenomicAlignments/IRanges
>                                    package
>                                                     does not take
>                                                                  into
>         account
>                                                                  cigars,
